  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Pool_Usage&quot; name=&quot;XE_Pool_Usage&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;XE_Pool_Usage&quot; name=&quot;XE_Pool_Usage&quot;>As-Is Models&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Partitioning not applicable at the Business level unless modeling the&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>as-is&lt;/em> viewpoints. And,&amp;nbsp;the&#xD;
    only the&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>as-is&lt;/em> models needed are at the Logical level or Technical level. The&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>as-is&lt;/em> models&#xD;
    are developed based upon existing documentation and/or research into existing operations. Therefore the Business level&#xD;
    is not needed ... these models are developed bottom-up. Since they are developed bottom-up, organizational structures&#xD;
    will be used to define the pools and lanes in these models.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    To-Be Models&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Partitioning&amp;nbsp;using pools and lanes is not based upon roles. Otherwise there would be no need for the&#xD;
    &lt;em>People&lt;/em> column in the framework. This is certainly not the case since there is a&amp;nbsp;definite need to&#xD;
    understand the structure of actors, roles and the required interfaces.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Business level&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Pools are useful for showing external client and “systems” interactions, and use lanes for functional (means of service&#xD;
    delivery) groupings (e.g., &lt;em>Research&lt;/em> or &lt;em>Publishing&lt;/em>).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Logical Level&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Use lanes for system components (sub-systems, legacy systems, COTS products) and pools for external actors and&#xD;
    systems.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Technical Level&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Use lanes for system components assigned to physical (specific) products and custom components. If there is messaging&#xD;
    between components/sub-systems then use pools instead of lanes. Use pools for the external actors, but clustered if&#xD;
    there are many of them.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
